1. Linker : It combines two or more separate object programs.
Hence, as the name suggests it collects and links different files for the generation of machine code.

2. Loader : It is responsible for taking maching code from secondary memory to primary memory. Hence, it allocates space in main memory and initiates the execution process.

3. Interpreter : It is a LANGUAGE PROCESSOR which processes the code directly without generating a machine language program. It directly reads,analyzes,and execute them on virtual machines.

4. Operating system : It is an INTERFACE between users and hardware of a computer system. It manages all resources of computer.